“'''Blue Lives Matter'''”（意译为“'''警察的命也是命'''”<ref>{{cite web |author1=林梅婕 |title=她喊「所有人的命都是命」遭槍殺 她寫「警察的命也是命」遭攻擊 |url=https://www.worldjournal.com/7044523/article-她喊「所有人的命都是命」遭槍殺/ |website=世界新聞網 |accessdate=2020-09-05 |language=zh-TW |date=2020-07-14 |archive-date=2020-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802051918/https://www.worldjournal.com/7044523/article-%e5%a5%b9%e5%96%8a%e3%80%8c%e6%89%80%e6%9c%89%e4%ba%ba%e7%9a%84%e5%91%bd%e9%83%bd%e6%98%af%e5%91%bd%e3%80%8d%e9%81%ad%e6%a7%8d%e6%ae%ba/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，亦作“'''蓝命贵'''”<ref>{{cite web |author1=王恺雯 |title=抗议办公室挂这面旗 她获赔10万美元-观察者网 |url=https://m.guancha.cn/internation/2019_04_21_498552.shtml?s=zwyxgtjdt |website=[[观察者网|观察者网]] |accessdate=2020-09-05 |language=zh-CN |date=2019-04-21}}</ref>）是一句{{tsl|en|countermovement|反制运动}}口号，起源于美国，其提出者认为任何杀害执法人员者皆应依照[[仇恨罪行|仇恨犯罪]]判刑。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/r-us-police-deaths-on-duty-spiked-in-2016-fbi-2017-10|title=FBI says US police deaths spiked 61% in 2016|publisher=Business Insider|agency=[[路透社|路透社]]|date=2017-10-16|first=Sarah N.|last=Lynch|accessdate=2020-09-05|archive-date=2020-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729093016/https://www.businessinsider.com/r-us-police-deaths-on-duty-spiked-in-2016-fbi-2017-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>此口号出自[[2014年纽约警官被杀案件|2014年12月20日纽约拉斐尔·拉莫斯、刘文健警官被杀案件]]，与另一平权运动口号[[Black_Lives_Matter|Black Lives Matter]]针锋相对。<ref name="DempseyForst2018">{{cite book|author1=John S. Dempsey|author2=Linda S. Forst|author3=Steven B. Carter|title=An Introduction to Policing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=K69EDwAAQBAJ|date=2018-01-01|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1-337-55875-4|page=34|quote="A pro-police movement called Blue Lives Matter was established in response to Black Lives matter and to the increasing attacks on law enforcement, which resulted in 63 officer line-of-duty deaths by gunfire in 2016."|access-date=2020-09-05|archive-date=2020-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918180329/https://books.google.com/books?id=K69EDwAAQBAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 社会影响 ==

受该口号影响，[[路易斯安那州|路易斯安那州]]通过了一个法案，将任何对警察、消防员、急救人员的攻击行为定义为仇恨罪行，不过这一法案遭到了[[美国公民自由联盟|美国公民自由联盟]]等多方的批评。<ref name="huffPoLou">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/blue-lives-matter-law-lousiana_us_588653dde4b0e3a7356ae3ae|title=Louisiana Police Chief Shows Why The State's 'Blue Lives Matter' Law Is So Dangerous|first=Julia|last=Craven|date=2017-01-23|publisher=[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]|accessdate=2020-09-05|archive-date=2019-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190210070304/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/blue-lives-matter-law-lousiana_us_588653dde4b0e3a7356ae3ae|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2020年9月，[[塔吉特百货|塔吉特百货]]店内一名在[[星巴克|星巴克]]工作的员工在[[TikTok|TikTok]]上传了一部“蓝命贵”影片，导致其被开除。影片中他手持一个写了“Blue Lives Matter”的星巴克杯子，往里面加入了清洁剂、冰块（暗指[[美国移民及海关执法局|美国移民及海关执法局]]，其英文简称是ICE，即“冰”）、蓝色的粉末，以及“无辜黑人的一点血液”（某种红色液体）。影片配乐是一首名为《圣诞节我希望警察死越多越好》（All I Want for Christmas Is More Dead Cops）的歌曲。塔吉特百货称，这一行为不尊重客人，在塔吉特百货是不可接受行为。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Greenspan |first1=Rachel E. |title=A barista at a Target Starbucks was fired for a satirical TikTok showing how to make a 'Blue Lives Matter' drink with 'bleach' |url=https://www.insider.com/blue-lives-matter-bleach-starbucks-barista-fired-for-drink-tiktok-2020-9 |website=Insider |accessdate=2020-09-05 |language=en-us |date=2020-09-03}}</ref>

